createLocations

protected Locations createLocations()
Creates an empty LocationsAndValue. This method overrides the corresponding method in PredicateList. The original returned a Locations which records every location of a variable in a PredicateList (a Query is a special kind of PredicateList). In addition, a Query can record the the current value of a variable. Thus this method returns an object that has no Locations and no Constant associated with any variable.

Precondition: none
Postcondition: result = new LocationsAndValue();

Overrides:
createLocations in class VariableInformation
Returns:
an empty LocationsAndValue.
